org.knime.base.node.meta.looper

Class ConcatenateTableFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.base.node.meta.looper.ConcatenateTableFactory

  • class ConcatenateTableFactory
extends Object
    Helper class that collects the rows of different tables. From these collection of tables a ConcatenateTable can finally be created.
    Since:
    3.1
    Author:
    Martin Horn, University of Konstanz

    • Constructor Detail

      • ConcatenateTableFactory

        ConcatenateTableFactory(boolean ignoreEmptyTables,
                        boolean tolerateColumnTypes,
                        boolean addIterationColumn,
                        boolean tolerateChangingSpecs,
                        Optional<Function<RowKey,RowKey>> rowKeyCreator)
        Creates a new factory that allows to create a ConcatenateTable.
        Parameters:
        ignoreEmptyTables - if empty tables should entirely be skipped
        tolerateColumnTypes - if the change of a column type should be tolerated (common supertype is determined)
        addIterationColumn - if an iteration column should be appended
        rowKeyCreator - an optional row key creator. If not provided, the row keys remain unmodified.
        exec - execution context mainly in order to create the new data containers

      • createTable

        BufferedDataTable createTable(ExecutionContext exec)
                       throws CanceledExecutionException,
                              DuplicateKeyException,
                              IOException
        Finally creates the ConcatenateTable. All data containers will be closed and no more tables can be added to the factory after this method call.
        Returns:
        creates and returns a table that wraps all the previously added tables.
        Throws:
        CanceledExecutionException
        IOException
        DuplicateKeyException

      • createSpec

        static DataTableSpec createSpec(DataTableSpec inSpec,
                                boolean addIterationCol,
                                boolean withMostCommonColTypes)
        Extends the given table spec by either appending another iteration column or setting the super columns types (according to the flags given in the constructor).
        Parameters:
        inSpec -
        addIterationCol - adds the column spec of the appended iteration column
        withMostCommonColTypes - creates a spec where all columns have the most common data type
        Returns:
        the data table spec possibly modified (e.g. an appended iteration column or more general column types)
